DESCRIPTION: Measure the voltage directly across the diode in the load module just before the lamp (across its anode and cathode), to determine if a large voltage drop is present across the diode that could indicate it is open or malfunctioning.,
RESULT: The voltage drop across the load protection diode is 0.359 V (anode at 0.3592 V, cathode at 0.0003 V). This voltage drop is typical for a forward-biased silicon diode. No indication of a large voltage drop that would suggest the diode is open or malfunctioning.
